                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d967">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">FW865.01/2197: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Harriman</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-03-14">March 14,
                            1944</date>.<lb/>[Received March 15—1:06 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>842. <hi rend="italic">Izvestiya</hi> for March 14 publishes the following Tass
                    despatch from Algiers dated March 13: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“On March 7, 1944, the Italian Government through the President of the
                            Council of Ministers, Marshal Badoglio, addressed to the Soviet Union a
                            request for the establishment of direct relations between the Soviet and
                            Italian Governments and for the exchange of representatives of the two
                            Governments. On March 11, 1944, the Soviet Government informed Marshal
                            Badoglio of its agreement to the establishment of direct relations
                            between the two Governments and the exchange of representatives.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Harriman</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
